In England, in the seven days to 19 November, there were 240,016 new confirmed cases (424.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 November, there were 213,997 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (26,019 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 24 November is 8,457,187 (14,955.2 cases per 100,000 population).
